or customize for your needs) ‚è± Timestamps ‚Äì Introduction: Building Your First AI Agent (No Coding Required!) ‚Äì Core Concept: LLM + Tools + Loop = Autonomous Agent ‚Äì Deep Dive: What Makes an AI Agent Different from Chatbots? ‚Äì The 4-Step Framework: From Simple Q&A to Autonomous Agent ‚Äì Claude Agent SDK Overview: The Framework We''re Using Today ‚Äì Agent Framework Landscape: Claude, OpenAI, LangGraph & More ‚Äì Quick Setup: Installing Claude Agent SDK (Python) ‚Äì Build Plan: Four Progressive Steps Explained ‚Äì Step 1: Foundation - Building a Simple Q&A Agent ‚Äì Step 2: Adding Memory - Making Your Agent Conversational ‚Äì Step 3: Adding Tools - Giving Your Agent Real-World Capabilities ‚Äì Step 4: The Agent Loop - Creating an Autonomous Agent ‚Äì Recap & Next Steps: What You Built & Where to Go From Here This is video 1 in our Agent Build Series. In upcoming videos, we will cover building agents with other framworks such as OpenAI AgentKit, LangGraph, CrewAI, and deploying agents to production. We will also explore advanced patterns like multi-agent systems, persistent memory, and real-world deployment strategies. The Claude Agent SDK makes building agents simple because it handles conversation management, automatic tool-calling loops, and streaming responses. What used to take hundreds of lines of boilerplate code now takes just a few lines. You can focus on building your agent''s capabilities rather than reinventing the wheel. More AI agent videos:', 'GritAI Studio', '', 1762724637, 1853, 7814, 170, 10, 0, '2025-12-20 07:17:09');
